 <sect1 xml:id="sec.admin.docupdates.sle12_sp1">
  <title>December 2015 (Initial Release of &productname; 12 SP 1)</title>
  <!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->
  <xi:include href="common_docupdates_sp1_i.xml"/>
  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 4. System Recovery and Snapshot Management with Snapper -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.snapper"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added information about the new <option>--sync</option> switch for
	<command>snapper delete</command> to <xref linkend="sec.snapper.manage.delete"/> (Fate #317066).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added <xref linkend="sec.snapper.snapshot-boot.identify"/> (Fate #317972 and
        Fate #318101).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added a tip to <xref linkend="sec.snapper.snapshot-boot"/> on how to
	do a rollback to the initial installation state or the state before a
	system update (Fate #317973 and Fate #317900).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added <xref linkend="sec.snapper.setup.customizing.new_subvolume"/>
	(Fate #318805, <link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=910602"/>).
	</para></listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>

   <varlistentry>
<!-- 5. Remote Access with VNC -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.vnc"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Turned a note into a section, added information about VNC using
        secured protocol by default (Fate #318936), and removed
        <systemitem>tightvnc</systemitem> as it is fully replaced by
        <systemitem>tigervnc</systemitem>. All in
        <xref linkend="sec.vnc.one-time.configs"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 6. Managing Software with Command Line Tools -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.sw_cl"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added <xref linkend="sec.zypper.ps"/> (Fate #318827).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added more examples of <command>zypper list-patches --cve</command>
        in <xref linkend="sec.zypper.softup.patch"/> (Fate #319053).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.zypper.softman.pluscontent"/> and a tip on
        removing all <systemitem>debuginfo</systemitem>packages in
        <xref linkend="sec.zypper.softman"/> (Fate #316287).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added a sentence on announcing the need for the system reboot after
        specific patch is applied. (Fate #317872).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- 11. journalctl: Query the systemd Journal -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.journalctl"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added section <xref linkend="journalctl.yast"/> (Fate #318486).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 12. The Boot Loader GRUB 2 -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.grub2"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated/simplified the whole chapter to match the latest GRUB
        version, both command line and &yast; version.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 13. UEFI (Unified Extensible Firmware Interface) -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.uefi"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.uefi.secboot.non-inbox"/> (Fate #317593).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 20. Basic Networking -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.basicnet"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Nanny is now on by default in
        <xref linkend="sec.basicnet.manconf.using_nanny"/> (Fate #318977).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.basicnet.router"/> (Fate #317121,
        <link
            xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=870132"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.ovs"/> (Fate #318497).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- 23 The Domain Name System -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.dns"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.dns.yast.expert.edit_master.rev"/>
        (Doc Comment #1356).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- 26. Sharing File Systems with NFS -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.nfs"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added tip saying that <option>--bind</option> mount is no longer
        necessary for NFSv4 mounts in
        <xref linkend="sec.nfs.export.manual"/> (Fate #316311).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 28. File Synchronization -->
    <term><xref linkend="sec.net.sync.soft"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Mentioned cloud computing for file synchronization.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>

   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- 29. The Apache HTTP Server -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.apache2"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Replaced <command>CA.sh</command> with the explicit
        <command>openssl</command> command in
        <xref linkend="sec.apache2.ssl.certificate.official"/>
        (Doc Comment #28367).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.apache2.multiple_instances"/> (Fate #317786).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the chapter to match the latest Apache version 2.4 (Fate #319012).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 36. Common Problems and Their Solutions -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.trouble"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Improved GRUB 2 re-installation procedure in
        <xref linkend="sec.trouble.data.recover.rescue.grub"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- Part II System -->
    <term><xref linkend="part.system"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="cha.kgraft"/> (Fate #313296 and Fate #313438).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Removed obsolete <systemitem
	class="service">acpid.service</systemitem> (<link
	xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=918655"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
	Fixed wrong title in <xref linkend="cha.kgraft"/> (<link
	xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=954250"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
	Fixed wrong path name in <xref linkend="cha.apache2"/> (<link
	xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=949395"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added a paragraph on secure boot enabled by default in <xref linkend="sec.uefi.secboot.sle"/>
        (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=879486"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Removed documentation about VNC view-only passwords in <xref linkend="sec.vnc.persistent"/> because they are	not available in
	&productname; (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=941307"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Fixed procedure to access the installed system in a rescue mode in
        <xref linkend="sec.trouble.data.recover.rescue.access"/>
        (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=918217"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added a new tip on updating the initramfs file after changing the
        default <command>sysctl</command> configuration in
        <xref linkend="sec.boot.initrd"/>
        (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=927506"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added a tip on preventing wicked from deactivating the network
        device on NFS roots in <xref linkend="sec.nfs.import-yast2"/> and
        <xref linkend="sec.basicnet.yast.change.start"/>
        (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=938152"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Fixed misleading statement about
        <systemitem>kernel-<replaceable>FLAVOR</replaceable>-extra</systemitem>
        in <xref linkend="sec.admsupport.kernel"/>
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=922976"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Btrfs/Snapper: Snapshots with new Subvolumes will not be Deleted
	( <link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=910602"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Btrfs Documentation on Separate Subvolume on /var/lib and
	Supportability ( <link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=930424"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
